The paper discusses the use of variational autoencoders (VAEs) and proposes a new class of objectives to improve their performance. VAEs are commonly used in machine learning for generative modeling, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of VAEs in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are both subcategories of AI. The proposed objectives aim to improve the quality of the variational posterior, which is a key component of VAEs and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents extensive qualitative and quantitative analyses, which are common in the subcategory of machine learning (cs.LG).
